article.description: — Bryan Greenlee had 23 points in Florida Atlantic's 101-73 win against Eastern Michigan on Sunday.
article.headline: Florida Atlantic defeats Eastern Michigan 101-73
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- — Bryan Greenlee had 23 points in Florida Atlantic's 101-73 win against Eastern Michigan on Sunday. Greenlee also contributed five rebounds for the Owls (7-1). Nicholas Boyd scored 17 points and added seven rebounds. Vladislav Goldin had 15 points and seven rebounds. It was the sixth straight win for the Owls. The Eagles (2-7) were led in scoring by Emoni Bates, who finished with 29 points and six rebounds. Eastern Michigan also got 15 points from Tyson Acuff and 11 from Kevin-David Rice. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
